# Demo Page Rules

All pages under `app/demo/**` use the showcase library from
`@/components/showcase`. They MUST NOT use raw `<h2>`/`<h3>` listings.

## Required template

```jsx
import { ShowcasePage, ShowcaseSection, ShowcaseVariant } from "@/components/showcase"
import { FooDemo, FooDemoStart } from "@/components/demo"

const crumbs = [
  { label: "Home", href: "/" },
  { label: "Demo", href: "/demo" },
  { label: "Magic UI", href: "/demo/magic" },
  { label: "Special Effects" },          // current page – no href
]

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <ShowcasePage
      title="Special Effects"
      group="magic/special-effects"
      crumbs={crumbs}
      description="Short overview of this category."
    >
      <ShowcaseSection
        id="foo"                          // matches anchor + manifest id
        name="Foo"
        description="What Foo does."
        docsUrl="https://magicui.design/docs/components/foo"
        sourceFile="components/ui/magic/special-effects/foo.jsx"
      >
        <ShowcaseVariant
          name="Default"
          exportName="FooDemo"
          sourceFile="components/demo/magic/special-effects/foo.jsx"
        >
          <FooDemo />
        </ShowcaseVariant>
      </ShowcaseSection>
    </ShowcasePage>
  )
}
```

## Section ordering

Order sections to match magicui.design's docs order for that category.

## Empty categories

If no components are installed yet, render `<ShowcasePage>` with
`{null}` as children and an honest description. The library auto-shows
the empty state.

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Using `<h2>`, `<h3>`, or the legacy `<Spacing>` component.
- ❌ Hardcoded `<Tabs>` / `<Card>` per variant. Use `<ShowcaseVariant>` only.
- ❌ Missing `id`, `sourceFile`, or `docsUrl` on a section.
- ❌ Duplicating the `Spacing` component definition in pages.
